commentary: Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Hope, no run big appeal They're thinking about a review but decide against it. Nicely flighted, the batsman took a few steps down the track and tried to play a big, booming drive, but was beaten and hit on the pads. The bowler seemed confident, but perhaps the batsman was too far down for Mashrafe Mortaza to chance a review

commentary: Rubel Hossain to Hetmyer, 2 runs dropped at short fine leg Short ball on leg, he swivels to pull it, Imrul Kayes found the ball coming to him almost before he was ready for it, burst right through of his hands, hit him on the chest and rolls away. Kayes seems to have been hit rather hard by that ball, and he's going off the field. It was well struck by Hetmyer, which contributed to it coming so quickly that Kayes couldn't react in time to catch it

commentary: Mahmudullah to Paul, 2 runs too short again, and pulled away again, and they run a hard two. West Indies have won Magnificent, magnificent knock by Shai Hope. It's the first win for West Indies on tour after two bad defeats in the Tests and one thrashing in the first ODI. But they have now levelled the series and there is all to play for in the last ODI.
